OL,11, The first suggestion for a computer    
OL,12, museum in Swindon was put forward by   
OL,13, Jeremy Holt in 1989 and received       
OL,14, encouragement from local computer      
OL,15, companies during the next decade.      
OL,17, However, it was only in January 2000   
OL,18, that serious progress was made with the
OL,19, establishment of a Steering Committee  
OL,20, and a company limited by guarantee.    
OL,22, The museum moved to its current        
OL,23, location in 2009.                      
